This paper deals with the application of active learning techniques to neural machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed methods also involve attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in neural machine translation and can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of applying the proposed techniques to image captioning, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV).
